      "side": 1,
      "message": "Why do this all in one step? Why not generate the .c file first and then use regular C/C++ build rules (with your additional -isystem flag) to compile the library? Take a look at https://android.googlesource.com/platform/frameworks/rs/+/master/Android.mk for how we handle generating a number of C source files just like this.\n\nYou can use LOCAL_GENERATED_SOURCES to pull in the correct C files that you just created (i.e. libsyscalls.c).\n\nMy main objection is that by doing this in one step with a pipe, you make it harder to debug any compiler issues in the future. You also propagate the knowledge of doing this the \"wrong\" way, where someone will happily copy/paste this and end up not getting the compilation they really intended (i.e. no one else should be explicitly pulling in TARGET_C_INCLUDES unless they have reason to).",
